NO_INITIALIZATION_CODE:
üö® CRITICAL: DO NOT GENERATE INITIALIZATION CODE (SYSTEM WILL BREAK) üö®

The preview system automatically handles React initialization. Your code must NEVER include it.

‚ùå ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN - Never generate these patterns:

1. ReactDOM.createRoot() calls:
   ‚ùå const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
   ‚ùå ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root")).render(<App />);
   ‚ùå const container = document.getElementById("root");
   ‚ùå const root = createRoot(container);

2. root.render() calls:
   ‚ùå root.render(<App />);
   ‚ùå root.render(<React.StrictMode><App /></React.StrictMode>);

3. ReactDOM.render() (legacy):
   ‚ùå ReactDOM.render(<App />, document.getElementById("root"));

4. document.getElementById("root") references:
   ‚ùå Any code accessing the root element for initialization

‚ùå EXAMPLE OF WHAT NOT TO GENERATE:
import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";  // ‚ùå Don't import ReactDOM

function App() {
  return <div>My App</div>;
}

export default App;

// ‚ùå NEVER INCLUDE THIS BLOCK:
const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root"));
root.render(<App />);

‚úÖ CORRECT FORMAT - Component definitions only:
import React from "react";
import { useState } from "react";

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-slate-900 p-8">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Counter: {count}</h1>
      <button 
        onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}
        className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg"
      >
        Increment
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;  // ‚úÖ Just export the component

üéØ WHY THIS RULE EXISTS:
1. The preview system (PreviewPanel.jsx) automatically adds initialization code
2. If you add it too, the code appears twice: "Identifier 'root' has already been declared"
3. This causes a SyntaxError and breaks the entire preview
4. Your job is to generate ONLY the component definitions
5. The system handles rendering and mounting automatically

‚úÖ WHAT YOU SHOULD GENERATE:
- Component definitions (function MyComponent() { ... })
- Export statements (export default App)
- Hooks and state management
- Event handlers and logic
- JSX markup and styling
- Imports from React and local files

‚ùå WHAT YOU SHOULD NOT GENERATE:
- ReactDOM imports
- createRoot() calls
- root.render() calls
- document.getElementById("root") references
- Any mounting or initialization logic

üîç VALIDATION CHECKLIST:
‚úì Did I avoid importing ReactDOM?
‚úì Did I avoid any createRoot() or render() calls?
‚úì Does my code end with "export default ComponentName"?
‚úì Is there NO reference to document.getElementById("root")?
‚úì Did I generate ONLY component definitions and exports?

If you violate this rule, the generated app will show:
